Picturesque 5.45-acre working farm on the banks of the Little Colorado River! This property features a fully renovated farmhouse (2010-new wiring, plumbing, insulation, mini-splits, and windows), plus a second historic block home, currently gutted and teeming with restoration potential. The working heart of this property includes two 12*24 storage rooms, a 20*36 workshop, a 12*24 cellar, and a chicken coop-perfect for storage, processing, crafting, or livestock care. Surrounded by a producing orchard (apple, peach, and pear trees), and holding valuable irrigation rights from the Woodruff Irrigation District, the land is fertile and primed for growing, grazing, or market production. Farm equipment, trucks, tractor, welder trailer, and other implements may convey with a compelling offer. Fully fenced and waiting for your vision, be it a hobby farm, commercial operation, or agritourism venture-every opportunity awaits! Woodruff's favorable climate allows for longer growing seasons, making this a versatile investment. Seller is motivated, will consider all serious offers, and open to trade.

Great opportunity to own a working farm on 39.87 acres adjacent to the Little Colorado River. This property includes two homes: a bunk house with 1,420 sqft., built in 1938, featuring 2 bedrooms and 2 baths, remodeled in 2010 with updated wiring, plumbing, insulation, mini splits, and windows; a block house with 1,247 sqft., a quarried sandstone home from 1938, currently in the remodeling stage and mostly gutted. The farm features a 9-acre parcel leased for cattle feeding and a 25.42-acre laser-leveled parcel for alfalfa. Additional structures include two 12x24 storage rooms, a 20x36 workshop, a 12x24 cellar, and chicken coop. Property also includes an apple orchard, fruit trees, irrigation rights from Woodruff Irrigation District,

This is a once in a lifetime opportunity to own a working alfalfa farm in rural Arizona! Six neighboring parcels convey with this sale. All parcels combined total 58.06-acres. Every acre comes with Arizona's oldest irrigation rights! Woodruff Irrigation District provides irrigation water. Approximately 54 acres are planted in alfalfa grass. Owners also currently lease and farm a neighboring 60-acre parcel. It is planted in a 4-way grass blend. Buyer to confirm if lease will convey. There is a newly constructed barn with attached home and 2 unfinished apartments, built in 2022 with mason block construction. Home is very comfortable with all the amenities and very quiet, well insulated walls throughout. Above the home, are 2 unfinished 750 sq ft studio apartments. These apartments would be perfect for farm worker's quarters or short and long term rentals. Each apartment is framed and has plumbing roughed in. The barn is 4500 sq ft and provides indoor storage for all the bales of hay that will be harvested! With the right offer, large farm equipment (including tractors and attachments) will convey. Private well is on the property but not currently in working order. Metered water to home is provided by Woodruff Domestic Water Improvement District. Additional parcel numbers to convey with this listing are as follows: 110-11-065P (6.09 acres) 110-11-065R (2.69 acres) 110-11-082 (32.52 acres) 110-11-079C (6.67 acres) 110-11-079D (1.70 acres) 110-11-076A (1 acre. Owners are currently in escrow to purchase this parcel.) Don't miss out on this beautiful turn-key farm in the beautiful green valley of Woodruff, Az. Woodruff is located only 13 miles from Holbrook, Az and Interstate 40 to the north and only 25 miles to Snowflake, Az and surrounding White Mountains to the south. Paved roads all the way there! Make your farming dreams come true, bring your family, and enjoy a new, slower way of life. Enjoy the 4 mild seasons and breathtaking sunsets rural Arizona has to offer!

Rare 9-acre irrigated parcel in Woodruff, AZ! This property has been laser-leveled and features a barn, corral, and irrigation system with gated pipe. Previously leasedout for cattle grazing. The land is planted with a mix of fescue, alfalfa, and clover- ideal for livestock, hay production, or hobby farming. Zoned A-General, you can build a site-built or manufactured home while enjoying wide-open space and agricultural income potential. Off-grid with no power or water currently on site, this property is a blank canvas for sustainable living or continued farm use. Located near the Little Colorado River, it's a unique chance to own productive farmland with room to grow. Seller is motivated, will consider all serious offers, and open to trade.

Where farmland meets the riverbank, opportunity flows. This rare 25-acre parcel along the Little Colorado River offers irrigated farmland with 7 irrigation shares, fed by Silver Creek. About 18 acres on the west side of the river have been laser leveled; ready for crops, pasture, or grazing. Build your dream home on the elevated portion while farming the lower ground. Irrigation typically runs March-Oct, with possible extended seasons. Quiet edge-of-town setting with state land bordering the northwest, minimal traffic, and power nearby. Excellent opportunity for farming, ranching, equestrian use, or future homestead. Woodruff's favorable climate allows for longer growing seasons, making this parcel a versatile investment. Motivated seller, will consider all serious offers, open to trade.
